Print Hex Values for Palette

Source: R/bi_pal.R
bi_pal.Rd

Prints the hex values for a specified palette.

bi_pal(pal)

Arguments

pal

A palette name; one of "Brown", "DkBlue", "DkCyan", "DkViolet", and "GrPink".

Value

A named vector with class values for names and their corresponding hex color values.

Examples

bi_pal(pal = "DkBlue")
#>       3-3       2-3       1-3       3-2       2-2       1-2       3-1       2-1 
#> "#3B4994" "#8C62AA" "#BE64AC" "#5698B9" "#A5ADD3" "#DFB0D6" "#5AC8C8" "#ACE4E4" 
#>       1-1 
#> "#E8E8E8" 
bi_pal(pal = "DkCyan")
#>       3-3       2-3       1-3       3-2       2-2       1-2       3-1       2-1 
#> "#2A5A5B" "#5A9178" "#73AE80" "#567994" "#90B2B3" "#B8D6BE" "#6C83B5" "#B5C0DA" 
#>       1-1 
#> "#E8E8E8"
